===Etymology===
From late {{etyl|enm}} {{term|sausige|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|xno}} {{term|saussiche|lang=xno}} (compare Jèrriais {{term||saûciche}}), from {{etyl|LL.}} {{term|salsicia|salsīcia|lang=la}} (compare Spanish {{term|salchicha|lang=es}}, Italian {{term|salsiccia|lang=it}}), neuter plural of {{term|salsicius|salsīcius|seasoned with salt|lang=la}}, derivative of {{etyl|la}} {{term|salsus||salted|lang=la}}, from {{term|sal||salt|lang=la}}. More at {{l|en|salt}}.

